                <zone forceUpdate='true' h='71935' id='17' type-v2='text' w='40074' x='44961' y='27181'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontsize='14'>Actions by metric:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontsize='14'>Automation Risk</run>
                    <run fontsize='14'> — Orange/red roles are at high risk of AI-driven displacement. Slow hiring and invest in retraining programmes.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontsize='14'>Net Job Change</run>
                    <run fontsize='14'> — Orange/red indicates declining demand by 2030. Avoid overhiring and explore redeployment options.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontsize='14'>Median Salary</run>
                    <run fontsize='14'> — Orange/red highlights below-market compensation. Review pay structures to retain talent.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontsize='14'>Remote Work Ratio</run>
                    <run fontsize='14'> — Orange/red indicates limited remote flexibility. Review office planning and hiring strategy.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontsize='14'>Gender Diversity</run>
                    <run fontsize='14'> — Orange/red signals underrepresentation. Prioritise targeted recruitment and inclusion initiatives.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontsize='14'>AI Impact Level</run>
                    <run fontsize='14'> — Orange/red indicates high AI centrality. Invest in AI upskilling for employees in these roles.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontsize='14'>Note: Values are aggregated across experience levels. Use the Experience filter to view metrics for a specific seniority level.</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
              </zone>
              <zone-style>
